description: Arizona's 2nd congressional district is in SW Arizona, including part of Tucson. Hillary Clinton beat Trump by 4.9% in this district. Sending letters to this district also helps in the crucial Senate race to replace Jeff Flake.

The 23rd district in Texas spans the southwestern corner of the state. Gina Ortiz Jones is the Democratic coandidate. She's an Air Force veteran and the daughter of a first-generation immigrant. By sending letters to TX-23, you're also helping Beto O'Rourke beat Ted Cruz.

Minnesota's 2nd district includes the suburbs south of Minneapolis. The incumbent Republican won his last election by only 6,655 votes. His Democratic challenger is Angie Craig, a former journalist and healthcare company manager.
Florida's 27th district is in South Florida, including parts of Miami. The incumbent Republican is retiring, making the seat highly flippable. Hillary Clinton won this district by a whopping 20%.

Pennsylvania's 10th district is in the south-central part of the state, including the city of Harrisburg. The district was recently redrawn, making the incumbent Republican even more vulnerable. The Democratic challenger is George Scott, a pastor and former army officer.

Ohio's 12th district is in the central part of the state, including the communities north and east of Columbus. The special election held on August 7, 2018 was extremely close. This seat is winnable by the Democratic candidate, Danny O'Connor, in the November rematch. Vote Forward volunteers sent more than 4000 letters to OH-12 in early August.

Georgia's 6th district includes suburbs north of Atlanta. The Democratic challenger is Lucy McBath, who lost her son to gun violence and was moved to run for Congress after the Parkland shootings. By sending letters to GA-06, you're also helping elect Stacey Abrams governor.

California's 10th district is in the northern San Joaquin Valley, including the city of Modesto. Hillary Clinton won the district by 3%. This flippable district is one of the California seats critical to a Democratic takeover of the House.
